==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Asunder
<hw>A*sun"der</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>a-</ets> + <ets>sunder</ets>.]</ety> <def>Apart; separate from each
other; into parts; in two; separately; into or in different pieces or
places.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I took my staff, even Beauty, and cut it <qex>asunder</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Zech. xi. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As wide <qex>asunder</qex> as pole and pole.</q>
<rj><qau>Froude.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Asura</ent>⟦br⟧
